{{Infobox military unit |unit_name=2nd Tactical Wing |image=2_Wing_(Belgium).png |dates=1947 |country={{flagicon|Belgium}} [[Belgium]] |branch=[[Belgian Air Force|Air Component]] |garrison=[[Florennes Air Base]] |march=Taïaut-Taïaut |mascot=A [[wild boar]] called Bullrush |commander1=Colonel Michel Colles |aircraft_fighter=[[F-16 Fighting Falcon]], previous; [[Dassault Mirage 5]], and the [[F-104 Starfighter]] }}
The '''2nd Tactical Wing''' ({{lang-nl|2 Tactische Wing}}, {{lang-fr|2 Wing Tactique}}) is a [[wing]] in the [[Belgian Air Force|Air Component]] of the [[Military of Belgium|Belgian Armed Forces]] at Florennes air force base in the Southern French speaking part of Belgium near the (small) city of Dinant. It comprises the [[1st Squadron (Belgium)|1st Squadron]] and the [[350th Squadron (Belgium)|350th Squadron]] of the Air Component.The 2nd wing has the famous patch/logo of a red comet ({{lang-nl|De komeet}}, {{lang-fr|La comete}})
