{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2013}} {{Infobox single | Name = Carry Me in Your Dreams | Cover = KejsiTolaCarryMeinYourDreamscover.jpg | Border = yes | Artist = [[Kejsi Tola]] | Released = {{start date|df=yes|2008|12|12}} | Format = [[Radio single]], [[CD single]] | Recorded = 2008 | Genre = [[Dance-pop]] | Length = 2:58 | Label = | Writer = Edmond Zhulali, Agim Doçi | Producer = Edmond Zhulali, Agim Doçi | Chart position = | Last single = | This single = | Next single = | Misc = {{Infobox song contest entry <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject Eurovision Song Contest--> | embed=yes | song = {{flagicon|Albania}} "Carry Me in Your Dreams" | image = | caption = | year = 2009 | country = Albania | artist = [[Kejsi Tola]] | as = | with = | language = English | languages = | composer = Edmond Zhulali | lyricist = Agim Doçi | place = 17th | points = 48 | place_semi = 7th | points_semi = 73 | lyrics = [http://www.diggiloo.net/?2009al from Diggiloo Thrush] | prev = Zemrën e lamë peng | prev_link = Zemrën e lamë peng | next = It's All About You | next_link = It's All About You (Juliana Pasha song)}} }}
'''"Carry Me in Your Dreams"''' was the [[Albania]]n entry to the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2009]], held in [[Moscow]], [[Russia]].<ref name="English">{{cite web|url=http://www.esctoday.com/news/read/13466|title=Albania: Kejsi Tola to sing Carry me in your dreams|last=Hondal|first=Victor|date=2009-03-08|publisher=''ESCToday''|accessdate=2009-03-08}}</ref> The song was composed by [[Edmond Zhulali]] and [[Agim Doçi]], composers of Albania's first entry to Eurovision, "[[The Image of You]]" by [[Anjeza Shahini]], and is performed by Albanian singer [[Kejsi Tola]] in [[English language|English]]. It finished 17th with 48 points.
==Background== The song was the winner of [[Festivali I Këngës 47]], the festival used to select Albania's Eurovision entry. Albania was the first country to select and publicly present its song. The song was chosen as the winner of the festival on 21 December 2008—five months before Eurovision, to be held on 16 May 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.esctoday.com/news/read/12771|title=Albania decided: Kejsi Tola to Eurovision!|last=Klier|first=Marcus|date=2008-12-21|publisher=''ESCToday''|accessdate=2008-12-21}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.oikotimes.com/v2/index.php?file=articles&id=4639 |title=Albania: Kejsi Tola chosen to sing in Moscow |last=Wells |first=Simon |date=2008-12-21 |publisher=''Oikotimes'' |accessdate=2008-12-21 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081224121911/http://www.oikotimes.com/v2/index.php?file=articles&id=4639 |archivedate=24 December 2008 |df=dmy }}</ref> The song was performed during Festivali I Këngës in [[Albanian language|Albanian]] as '''"Më merr në ëndërr"''' (Take me into your dreams), and the English version of the song was premiered on 18 March.<ref name="English" />
==At Eurovision== <!-- Deleted image removed: [[File:Kejsi Tola.jpg|thumb|left|200px|[[Kejsi Tola]] performing "Carry Me In Your Dreams at the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2009]] in Moscow.]] --> Kejsi performed the song at the Eurovision Song Contest 2009 semi-final on 14 May 2009, performing 16th in the running order, following [[Moldova]]'s [[Nelly Ciobanu]] with "[[Hora din Moldova]]" and preceding [[Ukraine]]'s [[Svetlana Loboda]] with "[[Be My Valentine! (Anti-Crisis Girl)]]". She received 73 points, placing 7th of the 19 competing songs, and qualifying to the final.
At the final on 16 May Tola performed 19th in the running order, following [[Turkey]]'s [[Hadise]] with "[[Düm Tek Tek]]" and preceding [[Norway]]'s [[Alexander Rybak]] with "[[Fairytale (Alexander Rybak song)|Fairytale]]". The song received 48 points, placing 17th of the 25 competing songs.
The staging featured two b-boys dressed as mimes (twin brothers) and a sequined green man (Jenia Evgenios Buli, who has performed with [[Kalomira]] in 2008 and [[Giorgos Alkaios]] in 2010). If only tele-voting had been used, Albania would have come in 11th.
