[[File:Domenico Giani 20070812.jpg|thumb|Domenico Giani in 2007]] [[Doctor (title)|Dr.]] '''Domenico Giani''' (born 16 August 1962 in [[Arezzo]], [[Italy]]),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://press.catholica.va/news_services/bulletin/news/18471.php?index=18471&po_date=03.06.2006|title=Nomina del Direttore dei Servizi di Sicurezza e Protezione Civile dello Stato della Città del Vaticano e Ispettore Generale del Corpo della Genarmeria|publisher=[[Holy See Press Office]]|accessdate=April 15, 2013|language=Italian|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120715121227/http://press.catholica.va/news_services/bulletin/news/18471.php?index=18471&po_date=03.06.2006|archivedate=July 15, 2012|df=}}</ref> ex officier of [[Guardia di Finanza]], is the current Inspector General of the [[Corps of Gendarmerie of Vatican City|Corpo della Gendarmeria]], the police and security force of [[Vatican City]], and the chief bodyguard of [[Pope Benedict XVI]] and of [[Pope Francis]]<ref name="cwnews newhead">{{cite news | url=http://www.cwnews.com/news/viewstory.cfm?recnum=44585 | title=New head for Vatican police | work=Catholic World News | date=June 5, 2006| accessdate=August 24, 2007}}</ref> since June 3, 2006.
==Biography== In 1999, Domenico Giani became the deputy to [[Camillo Cibin]], longtime chief of the Vatican's [[police force]], then known as the Security Corps of Vatican City State. Giani tackled [[Susanna Maiolo]] twice in two separate attacks on Pope Benedict during [[Christmas Eve]] [[Midnight Mass]] at [[St. Peter's Basilica]] in 2008 and 2009.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.catholictranscript.org/component/content/article/1172-vatican-to-decide-fate-of-woman-who-knocked-pope-down.html| title=Vatican to decide fate of woman who knocked pope down| date=December 28, 2009| first=Carol| last=Glatz| work=The Catholic Transcript Online| publisher=[[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Hartford|Archdiocese of Hartford]]| accessdate=December 31, 2009}}</ref>
Since June 3, 2006, Domenico Giani is the Inspector General of the [[Corps of Gendarmerie of Vatican City|Corpo della Gendarmeria]], the police and security force of [[Vatican City]], and the chief bodyguard of [[Pope Benedict XVI]] and of [[Pope Francis]].<ref name="cwnews newhead"/> He heads a unit of 130 military-trained policemen (2015).<ref>[http://www.lastampa.it/2015/02/28/vaticaninsider/eng/the-vatican/commander-of-vatican-gendarmerie-heres-how-we-protect-the-pope-3gkOPQMSHziiNnJT7Ex3lK/pagina.html Commander of Vatican Gendarmerie: Here’s how we protect the Pope], ''Lastampa.it'', 28 February 2015</ref>
