{{Infobox diocese | jurisdiction = Eparchy<!-- Type of jurisdiction: i.e. Diocese or Archdiocese --> | name = Barentu | latin = Eparchia Barentuanus | local = <!-- Name in the native language --> | image = | image_size = 200px | image_alt = | caption = <!---- Locations ----> | country = {{flag|Eritrea}} | territory = | province = [[Eritrean Catholic Archeparchy of Asmara|Asmara]] | coordinates = <!-- Use {{coord}} --> <!---- Statistics ----> | area_km2 = 44,986<!-- Area in square kilometers, automatically converted --> | population = 718,500 | population_as_of = 2008 | catholics = 40,794<!-- Number of Catholics in the diocese --> | catholics_percent = 5.7 | parishes = 13<!-- Number of parishes in the diocese --> | churches = <!-- Number of churches in the diocese --> | congregations = <!-- Number of congregations in the diocese --> | schools = <!-- Number of church supported schools in the diocese --> | members = <!-- Number of members in the diocese --> <!---- Information ----> | denomination = [[Eritrean Catholic Church]] | rite = [[Alexandrian Rite]] | established = 21 December 1995 ({{age|1995|12|21}} years ago# | cathedral = | cocathedral = | patron = | priests = <!-- Number of priests in the diocese --> <!---- Current leadership ----> | pope = {{Incumbent pope}} | bishop = [[Thomas Osman]], [[O.F.M. Cap.]] | bishop_title = [[Bishop]] | coadjutor = | auxiliary_bishops = | vicar_general = | emeritus_bishops = [[Zekarias Yohannes]] <!---- Map ----> | map = [[File:Eritrea - Eparchia di Barentu.png|250px]] | map_size = 100px | map_alt = | map_caption = <!---- Website ----> | website = | footnotes = }}
The '''Eritrean Catholic Eparchy of Barentu''' ({{lang-la|Eparchia Barentuanus}}) is a [[Eritrean Catholic Church|Catholic]] [[eparchy]] located in the town of [[Barentu, Eritrea|Barentu]] in [[Eritrea]]. It is a part of the [[ecclesiastical province]] of [[Eritrean Catholic Archeparchy of Asmara|Asmara]].
==History== On 21 December 1995, [[Pope John Paul II]] established the Eparchy of Barentu from the [[Eritrean Catholic Archeparchy of Asmara|Eparchy of Asmara]] and it became a [[suffragan]] of the [[Ethiopian Catholic Archeparchy of Addis Abeba]].<ref name=hierarchy>{{cite web|url=http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/diocese/dbrnt.html|title=Eparchy of Barentu (Ethiopian)|publisher=Catholic-Hierarchy|accessdate=2013-06-18}}</ref><ref name=GCatholic>{{cite web|url=http://www.gcatholic.org/dioceses/diocese/bare1.htm|title=Ethiopic Diocese of Barentu|publisher=Giga Catholic|accessdate=2013-06-18}}</ref> With the establishment of the autonomous ''[[sui iuris]]'' Eritrean Catholic Church by [[Pope Francis]] in January 2015, the Eparchy of Barentu became a suffragan the [[Eritrean Catholic Archeparchy of Asmara]].<ref name="Eritrean Catholic Church">{{cite web | url=http://press.vatican.va/content/salastampa/de/bollettino/pubblico/2015/01/19/0048/00098.html | title=Erezione della Chiesa Metropolitana sui iuris eritrea e nomina del primo Metropolita | publisher=[[Holy See Press Office]] | date=January 19, 2015 | accessdate=January 19, 2015}}</ref>
==Ordinaries== *Luca Milesi, [[O.F.M. Cap.]] † (21 Dec 1995 - 4 Oct 2001) *Thomas Osman, O.F.M. Cap. (4 Oct 2001 - present)
