{{Infobox World's Fair | box_width = | class = Specialized | image = | image_width = | caption = | year = 1985 | name = Expo '85 | motto = The creations of young inventors | building = [[International Fair Plovdiv]] | area = 5,8 Ha | invent = | visitors = 1.000.000 | organized = | cnt = 73 | org = | biz = | country = [[Bulgaria]] | city = [[Plovdiv]] | venue = | coord = | cand = | award = | open = November 4 1985 | close = November 30 1985 | prevexpo = [[1984 Louisiana World Exposition]] | prevcity = [[New Orleans]] | nextexpo = [[Expo 86]] | nextcity = [[Vancouver]] | suppl = Universal | prevsuppl = [[Expo '70]] | prevsupcity = [[Osaka]] | nextsuppl = [[Seville Expo '92]] | nextsupcity = [[Seville]] | simuni = | simspe = [[Expo '85|Tsukuba 1985]] | simhor = | simoth = | website = }}
'''The International Exhibition in Plovdiv (1985)''' was a world exposition that took place from November 4-30, 1985 in [[Plovdiv]], [[Bulgaria]]. The exhibition had the theme "The creations of young inventors". The specialized exhibition was the 24th held by the [[Bureau International des Expositions]] and the second held in Plovdiv.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.benemeritimilano.it/bie/storia.php|work=benemeritimilano.it|accessdate=2009-11-12|title=Breve storia delle Esposizioni Internazionali}}</ref> Another specialized exposition, [[Expo '85]] in [[Tsukuba]], [[Japan]] occurred the same year.
==Facts== *Participating countries: 73 *Visitors: 1,000,000.
