'''''Fano tesemara''''' ({{lang-am|ፋኖ ተሰማራ}}, 'O Guerrilla, rise to arms') is an [[Ethiopia]]n song. It was one of the most popular [[protest song]]s of the Ethiopian [[Student activism|Student Movement]] during the late 1960s.<ref name="p1">Bahru Zewde. ''[https://books.google.com/books?id=gZkSYR_fthsC&pg=PA13 Documenting the Ethiopian Student Movement: An Exercise in Oral History]''. Addis Ababa: Forum for Social Studies, 2010. p. 13</ref><ref>Tadias. ''[http://www.tadias.com/08/12/2010/part-two-exclusive-interview-with-ethiopian-legend-teshome-mitiku/ Part Two: Exclusive Interview With Ethiopian Legend Teshome Mitiku]''</ref> The song was inspired by the [[Cuba]]n and [[Vietnam]]ese revolutions, as manifested in its opening lines:<ref name="p1"/>
