{{Infobox company | name = Lukoil Baltija | logo = | logo_caption = | image = File:LUKOIL šalia Kalvarijos.JPG | image_caption = Lukoil Baltija petrol station in [[Kalvarija, Lithuania]] | trading_name = LUKOIL | native_name = | native_name_lang = | industry = [[Filling station|Petrol stations]] | predecessor = | successor = | foundation = {{Start date|1992|11|12}} | founder = | location_city = [[Užubaliai]] | location_country = [[Lithuania]] | area_served = Latvia, Lithuania, Estonia, Poland, Finland | key_people = | revenue = 724.05 .mil EUR <ref name=vz>[http://archyvas.vz.lt/news.php?id=44420260 Top 1000 LTU] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140116105102/http://archyvas.vz.lt/news.php?id=44420260 |date=2014-01-16 }}</ref> | operating_income = | net_income = | assets = | equity = | owner = | num_employees = | parent = [[Lukoil]] | divisions = | homepage = {{URL|www.lukoil.lt}} }}
'''Lukoil Baltija''' is a chain of [[petrol station]]s in the [[Baltic states]] owned by Russia-based [[Lukoil]].
In 2012, Lukoil Baltija was listed as the 4th largest company in [[Lithuania]] by annual revenue.<ref name= vz />
In 2015, Lukoil signed a deal to sell its 37 stations in Estonia to Aqua Marina, a subsidiary of [[Olerex]].<ref>[http://www.baltic-course.com/eng/energy/?doc=107025 Olerex buys Lukoil petrol stations in Estonia]</ref> In late 2015 and early 2016, Lukoil announced that its 230 stations are being sold in Latvia, Lithuania and Poland to Austria-based AMIC Energy Management.<ref>[http://integrumventures.com/en/newsview/amic_pokupaet_230_azs_lukoyl_v_litve_latvii_i_polshe Lukoil selling 230 filling stations in Lithuania, Latvia, Poland to AMIC]</ref>
In 2017, Lukoil Baltija was renamed Viada.
