[[File:Order of Duke Branimir.jpg|thumb|Order of Duke Branimir]]
The '''Order of Duke Branimir''' ({{lang-hr|Red kneza Branimira}}) is the 6th most important medal given by the [[Republic of Croatia]]. The order was founded on April 1, 1995. The medal is awarded for excellence in promoting Croatia in [[international relations]].<ref>{{cite journal | url = http://www.nn.hr/clanci/sluzbeno/1995/0377.htm | journal = [[Narodne novine]] | issue = 1995/20 | author = [[Croatian Parliament]] | language = Croatian | title = Zakon o odlikovanjima i priznanjima Republike Hrvatske | date = 1995-03-24 | accessdate = 2011-11-16}}</ref> It is named after duke [[Branimir of Croatia]].

Recipients of the order include [[Sir Fitzroy Maclean, 1st Baronet|Sir Fitzroy Maclean]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://narodne-novine.nn.hr/clanci/sluzbeni/2002_01_1_4.html |publisher=''[[Narodne novine]]'' |title=Odluka o odlikovanju (posmrtno) Sir Fitzroya Macleana Redom kneza Branimira s ogrlicom |date=12 December 2001 |accessdate=17 January 2011 |language=Croatian }}</ref> [[Milan Moguš]], [[Slobodan Lang]], [[Ante Kostelić]], [[Mike Moore (New Zealand politician)|Mike Moore]], [[Orrin Hatch]], and [[Luka Modrić]] among several other Croatian footballers.

