{{DISPLAYTITLE:''The Analyst'' (newspaper)}}
'''''The Analyst''''' is an independent<ref name="DahnStudies2008">{{cite book|author1=Kadiker Rex Dahn|author2=The University of Oklahoma. Department of Educational Leadership and Policy Studies|title=Learning from the Lives of Exiled Liberian Women: An Oral History from 1979 to 2006|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=dT--7n-00mcC&pg=PA45|accessdate=28 April 2012|year=2008|publisher=ProQuest|isbn=978-0-549-65942-6|page=45}}</ref> newspaper published in [[Liberia]], based in [[Monrovia]]. Run by two journalists, its aim is to "provide thoughtful, balanced news and encourage civil society in governance and the press".<ref name="EpsteinLimage2008">{{cite book|last1=Epstein|first1=Irving|last2=Limage|first2=Leslie|title=The Greenwood Encyclopedia of Children's Issues Worldwide|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=651lfiXk_pgC&pg=PA278|accessdate=28 April 2012|year=2008|publisher=Greenwood Publishing Group|isbn=978-0-313-33616-4|page=278}}</ref> It is considered one of the top sources for political issues in Liberia.<ref name="Streissguth2006">{{cite book|last=Streissguth|first=Thomas|title=Liberia In Pictures|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=P7fA6zZyHc0C&pg=PA35|accessdate=28 April 2012|date=1 February 2006|publisher=Twenty-First Century Books|isbn=978-0-8225-2465-6|page=35}}</ref>

